Docker compose is a tool to be installed on Docker host

Install Docker-compose on Lab

 curl -SL https://github.com/docker/compose/releases/download/v2.5.0/docker-compose-linux-x86_64 -o /usr/local/bin/docker-compose
 sudo chmod +x /usr/local/bin/docker-compose
  docker-compose --version

====================

Docker compose DEMO:
=======================

Create a compose file

mkdir composedemo
cd composedemo
vim docker-compose.yml

version: '3'
services:
 compose-test:
  image: centos:7
  networks:
   - compnet
  command: sleep infinity
  depends_on:
   - compose-db
 compose-db:
  image: redis
  ports:
   - '6379:6379'
  networks:
   - compnet
networks:
 compnet:


Press esc :wq!

# docker-compose up -d

# docker-compose ps

===============================

$ docker-compose exec compose-test /bin/bash 

OR

$ docker-compose exec compose-test sh

On the test container we need to ping DB container (6379)

To do this we need to install ncat package

$ yum install nc -y

netcat (often abbreviated to nc) is a computer networking utility for reading from and writing to network connections using TCP or UDP.




$ nc compose-db 6379




ping
+PONG

set name sonal
+OK

set day sunday
+OK

get name
$5
sonal

get day
$6
sunday

Ctl C

Exit â‡’ out of container

Stop & Delete all containers created using docker-compose file

$ docker-compose down

